🤫 What is the best kept secret about Cincinnati?⁠
⁠
It has one of the best park systems in the US.⁠
⁠
Seriously. It is chosen as one of the best park cities year after year because of their park equity, acreage, investment and amenities.⁠
⁠
Check out what some of their parks have to offer:⁠
⁠
If you're looking for a park to have a photo session go to Ault Park. It is known for its gorgeous Italian-Renaissance architecture.⁠
⁠
Want a little slice of wilderness? Head to Mt. Airy Forest. It's got 1459 acres of trails, gardens, picnic areas and a lake. It's perfect for hikers, runners and mountain bikers. The forest also has a host of bridle trails for horseback riders.⁠
⁠
Maybe you're more in the mood for panoramic views of the Cincinnati skyline and the Ohio River. Head to Eden Park. The hilltop locale, not only offers one of the best views of the city, you'll also find an indoor botanical garden that houses more than 3500 international plant species in glass Art Deco digs. The park’s also packed with arts and culture. You'll find the Cincinnati Art Museum here.⁠
⁠
If you want to know more about the parks in Cincinnati and why this hip city should be next on your list, head to the link in our bio and find out.

💃 Few countries can tick all the traveler boxes like Spain. ⁠
⁠
From its sun-drenched Mediterranean beaches, World Heritage cities, incredible cuisine, and multi-faceted culture, Spain has something for everyone.⁠
⁠
Wondering which city you should visit? Here's a rundown of what to expect in our favorites.⁠
⁠
🇪🇸 Madrid ⁠
Best city for visiting world-class art museums ⁠
⁠
🇪🇸 Barcelona ⁠
Best for modernist architecture⁠
⁠
🇪🇸 San Sebastián⁠
Best city for gourmet experiences⁠
⁠
🇪🇸 Balearic islands⁠
Best for beaches and sapphire colored waters⁠
⁠
🇪🇸 Seville ⁠
Best place for cultural sightseeing⁠
⁠
🇪🇸 Toledo⁠
Best for layers of history⁠
⁠
🇪🇸 Santiago de Compostela⁠
Best city for spiritual tourism⁠
⁠

node.text:
Imagine yourself here, looking across the Bastei Bridge at dawn with mist filling the valley of the Elbe beyond it.⁠
⁠
Bastei is the most famous rock formation in Saxon Switzerland, Germany and along with the bridge are the highlights of the german Saxon Switzerland National Park area.⁠
⁠
This is wonderfully rugged country where nature has chiseled porous rock into bizarre columns, battered cliffs, and carved deep valleys. Here, the Elbe courses through thick forest, past villages and mighty hilltop castles.⁠
⁠
It's a rock climbers paradise offering over 15,000 routes. While you could tick off the area’s highlights on a long day trip from Dresden, to truly experience the magic of Saxon Switzerland, you should stay overnight and enjoy a couple of good walks. ⁠
⁠
Want to find out more about the wonderful national parks in Germany? Visit the link in our bio. ⁠

node.text:
🏔 What's more challenging to hike in Peru than the Inca Trail? ⁠
⁠
The Cordillera Huayhuash.⁠
⁠
Lesser known than neighboring Cordillera Blanca and certainly not as popular as the Inca Trail, hiking the complete Huayhuash circuit has been noted as one of the most physically and emotionally challenging treks in the country.⁠
⁠
From extreme altitudes to breathtaking (sometimes literally so) views, it is also one of the most rewarding. ⁠
⁠
Are extreme hikes on your bucket list? Tap the link in our bio to find out what this one has in store for you.

node.text:
⁠
🌈 Don't you just love how colorful the buildings are in Curaçao?⁠
⁠
🎨 Fun fact: Curaçao’s buildings weren’t always so colorful. In 1918, Governor Albert Kickert complained of constant headaches that he attributed to the then-whitewashed city. He ordered all the buildings to be repainted in different colors. ⁠
⁠
(🤔 As it turns out though Kickert actually owned a paint company that made a lot of money off the new law. Now Curaçao prohibits their politicians from having private economic interests.)⁠
⁠
🌈  We're not complaining though. That's just one of the reasons we love visiting this island. ⁠
⁠
🏖 A second reason we love the island is it's located outside the hurricane belt, so traveling during storm season isn't as risky as it is in other parts of the region.⁠
⁠
Want to find out all the reasons we think this spot should be your next Caribbean vacation? Tap the link in our bio and you'll see.⁠
⁠
⁠

node.text:
Barcelona is home to some of Europe's most fantastic architecture.⁠
⁠
Building first boomed in the late Middle Ages, when Barcelona was seat of the Catalan empire. In the late 19th century, the city broke its medieval confines and was transformed through whimsical architectural movement called Modernisme.⁠
⁠
Modernisme was personified by the visionary work of Antoni Gaudí, a giant in the world of architecture. Imaginative creations by Gaudí and his contemporaries have filled Barcelona with dozens of masterpieces.⁠
⁠
Not sure where to begin your architectural odyssey? Tap the link in our bio for Barcelona's most beautiful buildings.⁠
⁠
Have you visited Barcelona? Which of these masterpieces was your favorite? Tag who you traveled with and let us know in the comments.

node.text:
Egypt brings out the explorer in all of us. ⁠
⁠
With sand-covered tombs, austere pyramids and towering Pharaonic temples, with its mighty Nile and magnificent monuments, Egypt welcomes visitors with its long past and storied history. ⁠
⁠
When starting to plan a trip to this ancient land, you'll  need this handy guide for the best times to visit Egypt. Save this to your inspo folder and tag your travel companion so you can make it happen.⁠
⁠
⭐️ High season: October to February⁠
Best time for sightseeing in balmy temperatures⁠
⁠
While much of the Northern Hemisphere is shivering and bundled up in heavy coats, Egypt’s winter is largely sunny and warm, with very occasional rain, though you might get some cool and cloudy days on the Mediterranean coast. There can be a real chill in unheated hotels along the sea, especially in damp Alexandria. The winter months in Egypt are peak tourist season, so expect high accommodation prices, especially between Christmas and New Year when many European families are vacationing away from the cold.⁠
⁠
⭐️ Shoulder season: March to May, September and October⁠
Best time for exploring without the crowds⁠
⁠
Tourist crowds are lighter in Egypt in the spring and fall months. Spring brings occasional dust storms, which can disrupt flights. The summer's warmth can extend all the way into October, making it a great time for quieter explorations and sightseeing. The Mediterranean and Red Sea coasts promise warm waters without having to get up early to stake out your patch in the sand.⁠
⁠
⭐️ Low season: June to August⁠
Best time for cooling off at the beach⁠
⁠
The scorching summer sun means only the hardiest sightseers visit the Western Desert and southern Egypt, where the average high temperature is a melting 108°F (42°C). The summer months are high season on the Mediterranean, when the weather is cooler than elsewhere, but the coast is crowded, and hotel rooms can be hard to find.⁠

node.text:
🌴 Set your internal clock to “Fiji time”: exploring the archipelago’s exquisite beaches, undersea marvels, lush interiors and fascinating culture shouldn’t be rushed.⁠
⁠
To help you plan when to go to Fiji, here’s our breakdown of what’s happening across the country, and what kind of weather you can expect.⁠
⁠
Who are you going to Fiji with? Tag them here so you can plan when to go. ⁠
⁠
⭐️ High season: June to September, December and January⁠
Best time for those tied to school holidays⁠
⁠
The high seasons coincide with the school holidays in Australia and New Zealand. Prices go up by 10% to 20%; costs peak in June and July. June and July are also the coolest, driest months, with pleasant temperatures.⁠
⁠
⭐️ Shoulder season: May and October⁠
Best time for milder temperatures⁠
⁠
The shoulder season includes the “Fijian winter” or dry season (May to October), bringing low rainfall, low humidity, milder temperatures and a lower risk of cyclones. Outside of high season you’ll frequently find useful discounts and lower walk-in rates.⁠
⁠
⭐️ Low season: November, February to April⁠
Best time for budget travelers⁠
⁠
November to April is Fiji’s wet season, with heavy rains and high humidity. There are fewer tourists in Fiji, and a greater chance of getting reduced rates on accommodation.
